@node Introduction "Introduction"

                          @{B}Introduction@{UB}

The "LightWave4 Unofficial Patch" is a patch which purpose is to fix
the lack of RTG support in LightWave V4 (Layout).
It's made to integrate CyberGraphX, the most widely used RTG system on
Amiga computers.

The idea to this patch came about in 1997, LightWave V5 had (finally) been
released for Amiga and I got hold of the last copy of LightWave V4 from the
Swedish distributor for a good price.
After a while I really started to get fed up by Layouts inability to be
promoted properly and it also annoyed me that such an expensive program
from 1995 not only was programmed in a non system compliant manner, it
had only basic support for PicssoII gfx-cards and no support for
CyberGraphX, which more or less was (is) the Amiga RTG standard.

In 1998 the work slowly began on LW4UP a patch that's been in progress on
and off since then and now finally has come to a state that is stable enough
for public release, and which I hope at least some people (besides me) will
have use for.
Even if LW V4 is now relatively old it's still a great program, not least
for mere mortals which do not produce "Jurassic" ;) projects for a living.
@endnode

