@node features "Features"

                               @{B}Features@{UB}

    * CyberGraphX screens can be directly selected from Options-Panel
      with ASL-Screen-Requester.
      Any screenmode from 672x432 (min. NTSC) and upwards can be selected
      in 8bpp, Hi or True color.

    * Last opened (CGX) screen ModeID is saved in ENV:/ENVARC: on exit
      and will be used on next startup.

    * It's possible to change from default Layout screen modes and CGX
      modes at will, if CyberGraphX can't be found or opened Layout will
      open on default screen.

    * Combined FeedBack/Status window on Layout, FeedBack is displayed
      in 32 grey-shades on 8bpp screens and in color on Hi/True color screens.

    * Make/Play Animation Preview's now work on CGX.

    * Color Requester window has got it's own pen, adjusting color values
      will leave UI colors unaffected.

    * Faster screen update when running on CGX, offscreen buffers are
      allocated with the same type & depth as Layout screen which makes
      a big difference when blitting buffers to screen and also when
      drawing lines (before, when promoting Layout, offscreen buffers
      did still get allocated in CHIP and therefore was using Amiga-Blitter
      when doing line drawing, it was further slowed down by the copying
      from CHIP to gfx-card memory).

    * ENV:LW4UP/notoast_prev (switch)
        For Toaster systems only; ON forces Animation Preview to be 
        displayed on Layout screen even if LightWave is started from
        Switcher, this is an experimental function and has not been tested.

      ENV:LW4UP/cgx_startup (switch)
        Main CGX switch; OFF forces Layout to open on deafult screen
        even if a valid CGX ModeID is found (if switch is ON and
        ModeID can't be found, ASL screen requester opens on WB)

      ENV:LW4UP/cgx_modeid (var)
        holds the last used CGX modeid (updated when LightWave exits)

    * A lot of 040/060 emulated instructions have been removed plus
      several other opt. gives a small increase in render speed
      (20-30% on 060), mainly when using proc. textures.
@endnode

@node requirements "Requirements"

                          @{B}Requirements@{UB}

    * LightWave V4.00y (original)

    * CyberGraphX V41+ (default screen will be used without it)

    * OS V39+ (for CyberGraphX)
@endnode

@node installation "Installation"

                          @{B}Installation@{UB}

There are two different install archives depending on what machine You own.
If You have an Amiga with 060 CPU use the archive named LW4UP060.lha, use
LW4UP.lha for all other Amigas.
The 060 version might render faster on machines with 68881/68882, this has
not been tested though.
Both version will run on any Amiga (with FPU) but the 060 version is
definitely not suited for 040 based Amigas.

Install searches TOASTER:Programs for either the file LightWave.FP
or LightWave.FP_old, if TOASTER: assign can't be found user will be
asked where LightWave are located.

If install finds (by checksum) that LightWave.FP is the original copy
it will be duplicated and named LightWave.FP_old, future installs will
do checksum test on first LightWave.FP and if that fails LightWave.FP_old.
It might therefore be convenient to leave the renamed original in place.

This will be created in ENV:/ENVARC:

    LW4UP/notoast_prev  -  for Toaster users only; if set this switch will
                           force animation previews to be displayed on
                           Layout screen.

    LW4UP/cgx_startup   -  if set, Layout (tries) to open in the screenmode
                           which are set in cgx_modeid var.

    LW4UP/cgx_modeid    -  install will set this var. to 0, this makes
                           LightWave open ASL screen requester on WB asking
                           for a valid screenmode.
                           It will be updated with the last used (CGX) modeid
                           every time LightWave exits.
@endnode

@node usage "Usage"

                          @{B}Usage@{UB}

A new "CyberGraphX (select)" choice will be added to the Option
Panels "Layout Interface" pop-up menu.
Selecting it will open a ASL screen requester with all non-suitable
CGX screenmodes filtered out.
Basically any screen with a min. resolution of 672x432 at any CGX
supported depth will qualify.

High res/depth screens will use a lot of video memory as offscreen
buffers also will get allocated in the same depth.
If Layout seems slow it's probably because buffers have been swapped
out to fastram, in that case close other screens or select a lower
res/depth mode for Layout (or both).

Rendering will be a little faster when using the default screenmodes
(with the annoying overlaid feedback/status screens).
Because the combined feedback window which is opened when using
CGX are updated with (system friendly) WritePixel() calls, this can
add a couple of seconds to every frame depending on how many passes
are done.
This will be changed in a future patch which will add the possibility
to turn off feedback, why it's implimented for other versions and not 
Amiga is somewhat odd, especially since there already seems to be
some preparation for it in the code.
@endnode

