@node faq "FAQ"

                                  @{B}FAQ@{UB}

******************************************************************************
    Q.
      There are no CyberGraphX choice in the Options Panel pop-up menu.

    A.
      LightWave couldn't open CyberGraphX library, it's either missing or to
      old, it must be V41 or higher. 
******************************************************************************
    Q.
      When trying to enter Modeler from Layout a grey screen opens with a
      requester saying "Can't enter Modeler - error 408."

    A.
      You are running Layout on a Hi/True color screen, Modeler can only use
      screens with a depth of 8bpp or less.
******************************************************************************
    Q.
      In doing Surface-Previews to HAM6 or HAM8 screens the surface name can't
      be seen, instead a light-grey bar are displayed underneath the surface.

    A.
      Only when running Layout on 8bpp screen will surf. names be printed
      correctly, OTOH will long surf. names often be mangled anyway.
      This fault happens with Hi/True color screens when printing text in
      COMPLEMENT drawing mode, it most likely are a fault in LightWave and
      not in CyberGraphX.

      -----------------------------------------------------------------------
      |If there are any demand for a CyberGraphX render plugin with Surface-|
      |Previev support I might consider making one which in that case would |
      |be "goodwill" software (with a small fee but uncrippled).            |
      -----------------------------------------------------------------------
******************************************************************************
@endnode

